properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Mass Naval flight of 41 planes from Pearl Harbor to the French Frigate Shoal; printed cachet at left, “Mass flight - 41 Navy planes; advance base operations - November 1935” and three signatures above and below; postmarked November 9, 1935 in Honolulu with football-shaped cancellation mark and U.S.S. Pelican, November 12, 1935 at Johnston Islands; backstamps: November 11, 1935 on U.S.S. Avocet at French Frigate Shoal, November 13, 1935 on U.S.S. Wright at French Frigate Shoal, and November 17, 1935 at Pearl Harbor.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “November 1935, mass naval flight”.
